'''Gijinka''' is a [[Japanese]] word meaning "humanoid", "personification", or "[[anthropomorphic]]", although the use of the word outside of [[Japan]] has come to be slightly different from the use of the word "anthropomorphic" in the [[anime]]/[[manga]]/[[furry]]/etc community. Rather than referring to just any animal with human characteristics, a gijinka is most often a [[fan]] re-design of an animal-like character from an [[animation]] or [[graphic novel]] in a human or humanoid form. (ex: a [[Digimon]] or [[Pokemon]]) Or of a humanoid version of the artist's own original animal-like character.


